obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE AGRICULTURAL PRODUCE (GRADING AND MARKING) ACT, 1937`
  line `A CT N O. 1 OF 1937 1`
  line `[24 th February, 1937. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the grading and marking of agricultural 2 [and other] produce.`
  line `W HEREAS it is expedient to provide for the grading and marking of agricultural 2 [and other] produce;`
  line `It is hereby enacted as follows:`
  line `1. Short title and extent. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called t he Agricultural Produce (Grading and`
  line `Marking) Act, 1937.`
  line `3 [ ( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India 4 * **. ]`
  line `2. Explanations. — In this Act, unless the contrary appears from the subject or context, —`
  line `( a ) “ agricultural produce ” includes all produce of agriculture or horticulture and all articles of`
  line `food or drink wholly or partly manufactured from any such produce, and fleeces and the skins of`
  line animals;
  line `( b ) “ counterfeit ” has the meaning assigned to that word by s ection 28 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860);`
  line `( c ) “ covering ” includes any vessel, box, crate, wrapper, tray or other container;`
  line `( d ) “ grade designation ” means a designation prescribed as indicative of the quality of any`
  line `scheduled article;`
  line `( e ) “ grade designatio n mark ” means a mark prescribed as representing a particular grade`
  line designation;
  line `( f ) “ quality ”, in relation to any article, includes the state and condition of the article;`
  line `( g ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( h ) “ scheduled artic le ” means an article included in the Schedule; 5 ** *`
  line `( i ) an article is said to be marked with a grade designation mark, if the article itself is marked with`
  line `a grade designation mark or any covering containing or label attached to such article is so marked;`
  line `6 [( j ) an article is said to be migra t ed if, —`
  line `( i ) the article is not of the quality prescribed for the grade designation with which it is`
  line marked;
  line `( ii ) the composition of the article offered for grading is altered in any way after a sample has`
  line `been drawn for analysis and determination of the grade designation of the article in accordance`
  line `with the rules made under this Act;`
  line `( iii ) the article is tampered with in any manner; and`
  line `1. The Act has been extended in its application to Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1965), to`
  line `P o ndicherry by Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3 and Sch. I (w.e.f. 1 - 10 - 1963) and to Goa, Daman and Diu by Notifn. No. G. S. R. 679, dated`
  line `1 - 5 - 1965, Gazette of India, Pt. II, Sec. 3 (i), p. 742.`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1942, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24 - 2 - 1937).`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for sub - section ( 2 ).`
  line `4. The words “except the State of Jammu and Kashmir” omitted by Act 25 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27 - 8 - 1960).`
  line `5. The word “and” omitted by Act 76 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15 - 4 - 1987).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. ( w.e.f. 15 - 4 - 1987 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
